HEPATITIS E - UK (02): EU PORK PRODUCTS, COMMENTARY
***************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Tue 23 May 2017
Source: Gideon (Global Infectious Disease Epidemiology Network) [edited]
http://www.gideononline.com


A recent posting in ProMED discussed the threat of hepatitis E related to pork products imported into the United Kingdom from France, Germany and the Netherlands. Indeed, all countries concerned have been reporting increasing rates for this disease in recent years - see graph [1] : https://www.gideononline.com/wp/wp-content/uploads/HepE.png

Reference:
1. Gideon Graphs Tool, https://www.gideononline.com/cases/multi-graphs/

--
Communicated by:
Prof. Steve Berger
Geographic Medicine
Tel Aviv Medical Center
Israel
<steve@gideononline.com>

[ProMED once again thanks Steve Berger and Gideon online for this information. Clearly zoonotic hepatitis E has become a significant issue in Europe. This virus is the only classical hepatitis virus that may be zoonotic in origin. - Mod.LL

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5057366,40.]
